The paper discusses randomized algorithms for low-rank matrix decompositions, which are commonly used in numerical linear algebra and machine learning. The use of the Subsampled Randomized Hadamard Transform suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) sub-category. The focus on approximation bounds and running time suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The use of randomized algorithms and analysis techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) sub-categories.
